## 📌 Overview
This module is part of a larger system and ensures synchronization between frontend and backend during an online assessment.

It maintains consistency in:
- 📝 Question State  
- ⏱ Timer State  
- 🔒 Submission State  

---

## 🎯 Objectives
- Real-time answer synchronization  
- Accurate timer management  
- Secure single submission  
- Immutable result handling  

---

## ⚙️ Features

### 🔄 Question State Sync
- Saves answers dynamically using `/save-answer` API  
- Prevents data loss  

### ⏱ Timer State Sync
- Timer controlled by backend (`/timer`)  
- Auto-submit when time expires  

### 🔒 Submission Control
- Only one submission allowed  
- Duplicate submissions are blocked  
- Answers locked after submission  

### 📊 Result & Feedback
- Displays score after submission  
- Highlights correct and incorrect answers  

### 🚫 State Consistency
- No answer changes after submission  
- No submission after time expiry  
- Results remain unchanged  

---

## 🔌 API Endpoints

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|----------|--------|------------|
| `/save-answer` | POST | Save user answers |
| `/timer` | GET | Get remaining time |
| `/submit` | POST | Submit final answers |
| `/result/{user_id}` | GET | Get locked result |

---

## 🏗️ Tech Stack

- **Frontend:** HTML, CSS, JavaScript  
- **Backend:** FastAPI (Python)  
- **Communication:** REST APIs  

